      <title>[PitsLamp short] Stop motion cinemagraph</title>
      <link>http://www.pitslamp.com/blog/20130424_pitslamp-short-stop-motion-cinemagraph</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.pitslamp.com/blog/20130424_pitslamp-short-stop-motion-cinemagraph</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pitslamp.com/images/blogposts/nespresso_trieste_napoli.gif&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://www.pitslamp.com/images/blogposts/nespresso_trieste_napoli.gif&#34; alt=&#34;stop motion cinemagraph nespresso&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I like stop motion, but it takes a lot of time. &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.saravdv.be&#34; title=&#34;SaraVdV: there are no endings, only new beginnings&#34; rel=&#34;muse friend met&#34;&gt;Sara&lt;/a&gt; needed some photos of the limited edition Napoli and Trieste of Nespresso and off course I&amp;rsquo;m the one making those. However having spend way too much time working at the computer lately, I decided to do something fun and combine a cinemagraph and stop motion, 2 things I love, but rarely get around to doing. After about an hour, this is the result. Enjoy&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
